					<head>Esther scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
							<note>
								<p>On the margin there are figures with musical instruments, bearing the names: בער, שמעון, חיים, הירש, וואלף, נחם.  </p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="border">
								<locus from="1r" to="1v"/>Partial borders between columns and outer margins, inhabited with floral and animal decorations, in colours. </decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 17th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>8 membranes, 14 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>468/505</height>
										<width>3825</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>8 membranes, with wooden roller. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Parchment hard and brittle, with many splits and loss of alignment.  </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="14" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible stiching of membranes. </p>
									<p>A few majuscular or minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 11 lines, in accordance with the rule. </p>
									<p>Wooden roller (505mm high). </p>
								</layout>
